    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240\u00baC/ 220\u00baC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spinach-and-caramelised-onion-tortilla-pizza/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste </strong>to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add 4 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spinach-and-caramelised-onion-tortilla-pizza/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>black olives</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spinach-and-caramelised-onion-tortilla-pizza/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach,</strong> then add it to a colander and pour<strong> boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spinach-and-caramelised-onion-tortilla-pizza/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> tortillas</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) and spread the <strong>tomato sauce</strong> evenly all over them</p><p>Top the tortillas with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spinach-and-caramelised-onion-tortilla-pizza/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>wilted spinach</strong>, <strong>sliced olives</strong> and <strong>sliced onion</strong></p><p>Dollop over your <strong>onion marmalade</strong></p><p>Drizzle everything with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 8-10 min or until the cheese has melted and the tortillas are crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>tortilla pizza</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spinach-and-caramelised-onion-tortilla-pizza/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the tortilla pizza[s] is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into the pan, cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spinach-and-caramelised-onion-tortilla-pizza/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>salad</strong> to a large bowl with your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and gently toss until the salad is coated</p><p>Season the <strong>fried egg[s]</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> tortilla pizza </strong>topped with a <strong>fried egg</strong> and the <strong>salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
